Jewelry Exhibits
The Extraordinary Jewelry of Alexandre Reza

Posted on October 31, 2013


 

The name Alexandre Reza is synonymous with exceptional gemstones and extraordinary design.  A major gem dealer and jewelry designer for over 40 years, the legacy of the Russian-born Reza, whose family is of Iranian origin, is best encapsulated in his exquisite jewels, twenty-five of which will be on view in New York next month.  From November 1st through 13th, Sotheby’s will honor the legendary Alexandre Reza, one of the greatest jewelers of the 20th century in the exhibition “The Extraordinary Jewelry of Alexandre Reza“.
Alexandre RezaPhotograph Courtesy Alexandre Reza via Town & Country
After his family fled the Russian revolution, they found a new home in France where the young Reza started his own jewelry and antiques business.  With his willful spirit and enduring determination, Reza keenly cultivated his reputation for dealing in the most exceptional stones, making him a key supplier to Place Vendôme’s master jewelers in the 1960s and 70s.  The following decade, instead of retiring, Reza opened his own shop in the Place Vendôme where he offered his marvelous gems in masterful designs of his own making.
In the 1950s and ’60s, Alexandre Reza was the man Harry Winston, Cartier, and Boucheron turned to when a client requested a particularly rare piece.Photograph Courtesy of Alexandre Reza via Town & Country
Though the boutique was closed in 2008, Reza’s son Olivier has brilliantly revived his father’s business by offering his contemporary designs alongside his father’s archival pieces, both of which will be featured in Sotheby’s exhibition.  Together, the pieces in the exhibition are a mesmerizing peek into Reza’s splendid vaults, which are rumored to house one of the world’s largest and most impressive private collections of gemstones and jewels.
Alexandre Reza by Vivienne BeckerPhoto courtesy of Assouline
David Bennett, Chairman of Sotheby’s Jewelry Division Europe & Middle East, comments: “Alexandre Reza’s legacy forms an integral and important part of the history of post war jewelry. Sotheby’s is honored to showcase his work through this special exhibition, which will include many of the most important jewels and parures created by Alexandre Reza during the last 40 years, featuring spectacular diamonds, natural pearls and superb colored gems. We are particularly thrilled to support his son Olivier as he carries the Reza name to the next generation of collectors and connoisseurs with his exciting new designs.”
Photo courtesy of Alexandre Reza via Sotheby’s
Highlights of the exhibition include several of Reza’s iconic parures, set with impressively-sized emeralds and sapphires, the remarkable “Notre Dame” clip featuring a 133.63-carat unheated Ceylon sapphire and a magnificent ring with a 52.31-carat Burmese sapphire flanked by a double bombé mounting swathed with diamonds.
In 2014, the exhibition will travel to Sotheby’s offices around the world, including Beijing, Doha and London.
Gold, Natural Pearl and Diamond “Le Carcan” Necklace, Alexandre Reza
Gold, Natural Pearl and Diamond “Le Carcan” Necklace, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
Historically-inspired gold necklace set with 11 variously cut diamonds of 37.11 carats, the intricate goldwork delicately accented by 154 natural pearls, 1983.
Photo courtesy of Sotheby’s
 
Gold, Diamond, Yellow Diamond and Sapphire “Notre Dame” Clip, Alexandre Reza
Gold, Diamond, Yellow Diamond and Sapphire “Notre Dame” Clip, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The extraordinary “Notre Dame” clip set with an unheated oval-shaped Ceylon sapphire of 133.63 carats, along with 14 round diamonds weighing 16.95 carats, bordered by 14 pear-shaped sapphires of 8.22 carats, further accented by 49 yellow diamonds of 1.60 carats and completed at the top with a pear-shaped diamond of .94 carat, 1980.
 
A Superb Suite of Gold Emerald and Diamond Jewelry, Alexandre Reza
A Superb Suite of Gold Emerald and Diamond Jewelry, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
Superb parure of classical design.  The necklace features 7 emerald-cut Colombian emeralds weighing 24.98 carats, finished by 78 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 19.92 carats.  The bracelet with 8 Colombian emeralds weighing 15.41 carats, accented by 24 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 7.17 carats.  The earrings suspending 2 emerald-cut emeralds weighing 7.07 carats, topped with 6 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 2.21 carats.  The ring centered by an emerald-cut Colombian emerald of 5.55 carats, surrounded by 4 round diamonds of .43 carat.
 
A Highly Important Suite of Gold, Sapphire and Diamond Jewelry, Alexandre Reza
A Highly Important Suite of Gold, Sapphire and Diamond Jewelry, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
Highly important sapphire and diamond suite, the necklace featuring 600 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 82.93 carats, set with 9 unheated emerald-cut Burmese and Ceylon sapphires weighing 151.45 carats.  The ring centered by an unheated emerald-cut Burmese sapphire of 31.93 carats, surrounded by 26 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 4.39 carats. The bracelet set with 5 unheated emerald-cut Ceylon sapphires weighing 44.76 carats, surrounded by 115 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 11.96 carats.  The earrings suspending 2 unheated emerald-cut Ceylon sapphires of 15.82 carats, along with 60 round and emerald-cut diamonds weighing 6.87 carats, 1981.
 
A Magnificent Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Ring, Alexandre Reza
A Magnificent Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Ring, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The spectacular ring featuring an unheated oval-shaped Burmese sapphire weighing 52.31 carats, supported by a double bombé mounting set with 101 oval-shaped diamonds weighing 28.02 carats, 1975.
 
An Exceptional Gold, Emerald and Diamond “Trembleur” Suite, Alexandre Reza
An Exceptional Gold, Emerald and Diamond “Trembleur” Suite, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The exceptional and expertly executed “trembleur” emerald suite, the necklace features 3 emerald-cut emeralds of 8.24 carats, 30 D color, Internally Flawless pear-shaped diamonds of 36.25 carats, and 135 additional round brilliant, pear-shaped and navette-shaped diamonds weighing 21.66 carats.  Bracelet is composed of an emerald-cut emerald of 3.12 carats, along with 10 predominantly D color, Internally Flawless pear-shaped diamonds of 11.22 carats, and completed by 95 pear-shaped diamonds weighing 23.62 carats.  The earrings feature 4 emerald-cut emeralds weighing a total of 6.37 carats surrounded by 20 predominantly D color, Internally Flawless pear-shaped diamonds weighing approximately 16.19 carats, further accented by 42 round brilliant, pear-shaped and navette-shaped diamonds weighing approximately 6.48 carats, 1979.
 
A Magnificent Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Choker, Alexandre Reza
A Magnificent Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Choker, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The magnificent sapphire choker composed of 5 unheated oval-shaped Ceylon sapphires weighing 146.10 carats, surrounded by 486 round diamonds of 133.32 carats, 1975.
 
An Extraordinary Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Bird Clip, Alexandre Reza
An Extraordinary Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Bird Clip, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The extraordinary stylized bird clip composed of an unheated “disco” cut Ceylon sapphire weighing 54.70 carats, and completed with 149 oval and pear-shaped diamonds weighing 34.69 carats, 1975.
 
Pair of Gold, Diamond, Yellow Diamond and Emerald “Manhattan” Earrings, Alexandre Reza
Pair of Gold, Diamond, Yellow Diamond and Emerald “Manhattan” Earrings, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The architecturally inspired “Manhattan” earrings centering 2 emerald-cut Colombian emeralds of 10.85 and 11.46 carats each, 2 Fancy Intense Yellow cushion-cut diamonds of 2.78 and 2.85 carats each, 2 princess-cut diamonds of 1.04 and .96 carats each, diamond baguettes of 16.20 carats, and round diamonds weighing approximately 3 carats, 1998.
 
Natural Pearl, Diamond and Yellow Diamond “Rose Perlée” Necklace, Alexandre Reza
Natural Pearl, Diamond and Yellow Diamond “Rose Perlée” Necklace, Alexandre RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The elegant “rose perlée” necklace set with a Fancy Intense Yellow diamond weighing 2.49 carats and bordered by 3 rose-cut diamonds weighing 12.22 carats, suspending an impressive drop shaped natural pearl, completed by 5 strands of natural pearls, 1996.
 
Pair of Blackened Gold and Diamond Earrings, Olivier Reza
Pair of Blackened Gold and Diamond Earrings, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The sculptural crescents set with 212 round diamonds weighing 9.01 carats, bordered by 64 diamond rondelles weighing 6.42 carats and topped with 2 modified triangular-cut diamonds of 1.48 carats, mounted in blackened white gold, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Gold, Emerald and Diamond Ring, Olivier Reza
Gold, Emerald and Diamond Ring, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The impressive geometric ring featuring an emerald-cut diamond weighing 9.88 carats and framed by 2 half-moon shaped Colombian emeralds weighing 11.44 carats, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Pair of Platinum, Emerald and Diamond Earrings, Olivier Reza
Pair of Platinum, Emerald and Diamond Earrings, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The highly important earrings suspending 4 oval-shaped Colombian emeralds weighing a total of 51.84 carats, framed by 428 variously shaped diamonds of 17.95 carats, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Pair of Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Earrings, Olivier Reza
Pair of Platinum, Sapphire and Diamond Earrings, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The remarkable earrings centered by 2 unheated oval-shaped Ceylon sapphires weighing 13.04 and 12.15 carats and 2 marquise-shaped diamonds weighing 2.40 and 2.08 carats, further accented by numerous baguette diamonds and sapphires, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Gold, Natural Pearl, Diamond and Colored Diamond Necklace, Olivier Reza
Gold, Natural Pearl, Diamond and Colored Diamond Necklace, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
Suspending an extraordinary natural grey drop-shaped pearl, the elegant sautoir composed of 12 princess-cut diamonds weighing 6.66 carats, 455 round brilliant diamonds weighing 5.79 carats accented by 10 natural pearls, joined in the center by a lozenge-shaped diamond of 1.18 carats  and a trapeze-cut Fancy Deep Orange Yellow diamond of 3.76 carats , design by Olivier Reza.
 
Pair of Blackened Gold, Natural Pearl, Diamond and Colored Diamond Earclips, Olivier Reza
Pair of Blackened Gold, Natural Pearl, Diamond and Colored Diamond Earclips, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The graceful blackened white gold branches finished by flowerheads composed of 33 pear-shaped Fancy Vivid Yellow diamonds weighing 7.33 carats, 10 marquise-cut diamonds weighing 1.77 carats, 12 round brilliant diamonds weighing .74 carat, 12 pear-shaped diamonds weighing 1.58 carats, further accented by 12 natural pearls, finished at the tops by 2 larger natural pearls of grey and creamy-white hue, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Platinum, Fancy Vivid Blue Diamond and Diamond “Toi et Moi” Ring, Olivier Reza
Platinum, Fancy Vivid Blue Diamond and Diamond “Toi et Moi” Ring, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The magnificent pear-shaped Fancy Vivid Blue, Internally Flawless diamond weighing 5.35 carats matched with a pear-shaped D color, Internally Flawless diamond of 5.42 carats, design by Olivier Reza.
 
Red Gold, Fancy Pink Diamond and Emerald “Toi et Moi” Ring, Olivier Reza
Red Gold, Fancy Pink Diamond and Emerald “Toi et Moi” Ring, Olivier RezaPhoto courtesy of Sotheby’s
The pear-shaped Fancy Pink, Internally Flawless diamond of 5.04 carats gracefully juxtaposed with a pear-shaped emerald of exceptional color weighing 4.76 carats, design by Olivier Reza.
 



